RAM types : 
 soldered RAM --> built in with mother board , if you want to replace it you must change the whole mother board 
 SO-DIMM --> removable memory that can be replaced ( it is held in place by clips within its slots ) 
Storage types : 
 HDD (hard drive) --> magnetic disk , spinning drive platter (slower because it depends on physical movement to read data)
 SSD (solid state drive) --> no moving parts , more speed , less latency , smaller than HDD 





